        <num>CC 1746</num>
        <heading>1746.  Objects and beneficiaries</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1746.  Objects and beneficiaries
The donation, which may consist of any of the donor's present property or all or any of the property that the donor will leave at his death, may be made to the donor's future or present spouse.  The donation may not, however, be made to their common descendants, whether already born or to be born.</p>
        </content>
